Akure – As Ondo State chapter of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has concluded plans on the second annual lecture of its Support Group, Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State would lead chieftains of the party to the event in Akure, Ondo State capital on Wednesday next week. Makinde, who is the Special Guest of Honour, would address party members at the lecture which focused on how the party could leverage on the trust and confidence of the members and supporters of the party to record electoral victory in 2020 governorship elections in the state and the country at large. According to a statement by the group’s coordinator, Bode Obanla, said the state party chairman, Clement Faboyede would be the chief host of the event. “The 2019 edition of the annual lecture tagged ‘PDP: Harnessing the Trust of the People’, will have as guest speakers, PDP’s National Publicity Secretary, Kola Ologbondiyan; Spokesperson of the Atiku Campaign Organisation, Segun Sowunmi, and a chieftain of the party in Ondo State, Akogun Tokunbo Modupe,” the statement read. Obanla described the victory of Governor Makinde at the Election Petitions Tribunal as confirmation of the popularity and love of the governor among the people of Oyo State. He, however, expressed confidence in the governor, saying “We have no doubt that Makinde, like other governors elected on the platform of our party will make the people proud as he is already doing in barely four months after his inauguration.”